38template <bool isPureInteger>
39ColorGeneric ConvertToColor(const GLfloat *params)
40{
41 if (isPureInteger)
42 {
43 UNREACHABLE();
44 return ColorGeneric(ColorI());
45 }
46 else
47 {
48 return ColorGeneric(ColorF::fromData(params));
49 }
50}
51
52template <bool isPureInteger>
53ColorGeneric ConvertToColor(const GLint *params)
54{
55 if (isPureInteger)
56 {
57 return ColorGeneric(ColorI(params[0], params[1], params[2], params[3]));
58 }
59 else
60 {
61 return ColorGeneric(ColorF(normalizedToFloat(params[0]), normalizedToFloat(params[1]),
62 normalizedToFloat(params[2]), normalizedToFloat(params[3])));
63 }
64}
65
66template <bool isPureInteger>
67ColorGeneric ConvertToColor(const GLuint *params)
68{
69 if (isPureInteger)
70 {
71 return ColorGeneric(ColorUI(params[0], params[1], params[2], params[3]));
72 }
73 else
74 {
75 UNREACHABLE();
76 return ColorGeneric(ColorF());
77 }
78}
79
80template <bool isPureInteger>
81void ConvertFromColor(const ColorGeneric &color, GLfloat *outParams)
82{
83 if (isPureInteger)
84 {
85 UNREACHABLE();
86 }
87 else
88 {
89 ASSERT(color.type == ColorGeneric::Type::Float);
90 color.colorF.writeData(outParams);
91 }
92}
93
94template <bool isPureInteger>
95void ConvertFromColor(const ColorGeneric &color, GLint *outParams)
96{
97 if (isPureInteger)
98 {
99 ASSERT(color.type == ColorGeneric::Type::Int);
100 outParams[0] = color.colorI.red;
101 outParams[1] = color.colorI.green;
102 outParams[2] = color.colorI.blue;
103 outParams[3] = color.colorI.alpha;
104 }
105 else
106 {
107 ASSERT(color.type == ColorGeneric::Type::Float);
108 outParams[0] = floatToNormalized<GLint>(color.colorF.red);
109 outParams[1] = floatToNormalized<GLint>(color.colorF.green);
110 outParams[2] = floatToNormalized<GLint>(color.colorF.blue);
111 outParams[3] = floatToNormalized<GLint>(color.colorF.alpha);
112 }
113}
114
115template <bool isPureInteger>
116void ConvertFromColor(const ColorGeneric &color, GLuint *outParams)
117{
118 if (isPureInteger)
119 {
120 ASSERT(color.type == ColorGeneric::Type::UInt);
121 outParams[0] = color.colorUI.red;
122 outParams[1] = color.colorUI.green;
123 outParams[2] = color.colorUI.blue;
124 outParams[3] = color.colorUI.alpha;
125 }
126 else
127 {
128 UNREACHABLE();
129 }
130}

132template <typename ParamType>
133void QueryTexLevelParameterBase(const Texture *texture,
134 TextureTarget target,
135 GLint level,
136 GLenum pname,
137 ParamType *params)
138{
139 ASSERT(texture != nullptr);
140 const InternalFormat *info = texture->getTextureState().getImageDesc(target, level).format.info;
141
142 switch (pname)
143 {
144 case GL_TEXTURE_RED_TYPE:
145 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(
146 pname, info->redBits ? info->componentType : GL_NONE);
147 break;
148 case GL_TEXTURE_GREEN_TYPE:
149 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(
150 pname, info->greenBits ? info->componentType : GL_NONE);
151 break;
152 case GL_TEXTURE_BLUE_TYPE:
153 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(
154 pname, info->blueBits ? info->componentType : GL_NONE);
155 break;
156 case GL_TEXTURE_ALPHA_TYPE:
157 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(
158 pname, info->alphaBits ? info->componentType : GL_NONE);
159 break;
160 case GL_TEXTURE_DEPTH_TYPE:
161 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(
162 pname, info->depthBits ? info->componentType : GL_NONE);
163 break;
164 case GL_TEXTURE_RED_SIZE:
165 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, info->redBits);
166 break;
167 case GL_TEXTURE_GREEN_SIZE:
168 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, info->greenBits);
169 break;
170 case GL_TEXTURE_BLUE_SIZE:
171 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, info->blueBits);
172 break;
173 case GL_TEXTURE_ALPHA_SIZE:
174 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, info->alphaBits);
175 break;
176 case GL_TEXTURE_DEPTH_SIZE:
177 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, info->depthBits);
178 break;
179 case GL_TEXTURE_STENCIL_SIZE:
180 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, info->stencilBits);
181 break;
182 case GL_TEXTURE_SHARED_SIZE:
183 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, info->sharedBits);
184 break;
185 case GL_TEXTURE_INTERNAL_FORMAT:
186 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(
187 pname, info->internalFormat ? info->internalFormat : GL_RGBA);
188 break;
189 case GL_TEXTURE_WIDTH:
190 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(
191 pname, static_cast<uint32_t>(texture->getWidth(target, level)));
192 break;
193 case GL_TEXTURE_HEIGHT:
194 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(
195 pname, static_cast<uint32_t>(texture->getHeight(target, level)));
196 break;
197 case GL_TEXTURE_DEPTH:
198 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(
199 pname, static_cast<uint32_t>(texture->getDepth(target, level)));
200 break;
201 case GL_TEXTURE_SAMPLES:
202 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getSamples(target, level));
203 break;
204 case GL_TEXTURE_FIXED_SAMPLE_LOCATIONS:
205 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(
206 pname, static_cast<GLint>(texture->getFixedSampleLocations(target, level)));
207 break;
208 case GL_TEXTURE_COMPRESSED:
209 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(pname, static_cast<GLint>(info->compressed));
210 break;
211 case GL_MEMORY_SIZE_ANGLE:
212 *params =
213 CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getLevelMemorySize(target, level));
214 break;
215 case GL_RESOURCE_INITIALIZED_ANGLE:
216 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(
217 pname, texture->initState(ImageIndex::MakeFromTarget(target, level)) ==
218 InitState::Initialized);
219 break;
220 case GL_TEXTURE_BUFFER_DATA_STORE_BINDING:
221 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(
222 pname, static_cast<GLint>(texture->getBuffer().id().value));
223 break;
224 case GL_TEXTURE_BUFFER_OFFSET:
225 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(
226 pname, static_cast<GLint>(texture->getBuffer().getOffset()));
227 break;
228 case GL_TEXTURE_BUFFER_SIZE:
229 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(
230 pname, static_cast<GLint>(texture->getBuffer().getSize()));
231 break;
232 default:
233 UNREACHABLE();
234 break;
235 }
236}

238// This function is needed to handle fixed_point data.
239// It can be used when some pname need special conversion from int/float/bool to fixed_point.
240template <bool isGLfixed, typename QueryT, typename ParamType>
241QueryT CastFromSpecialValue(GLenum pname, const ParamType param)
242{
243 if (isGLfixed)
244 {
245 return static_cast<QueryT>(ConvertFloatToFixed(CastFromStateValue<GLfloat>(pname, param)));
246 }
247 else
248 {
249 return CastFromStateValue<QueryT>(pname, param);
250 }
251}

253template <bool isPureInteger, bool isGLfixed, typename ParamType>
254void QueryTexParameterBase(const Context *context,
255 const Texture *texture,
256 GLenum pname,
257 ParamType *params)
258{
259 ASSERT(texture != nullptr);
260
261 switch (pname)
262 {
263 case GL_TEXTURE_MAG_FILTER:
264 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getMagFilter());
265 break;
266 case GL_TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER:
267 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getMinFilter());
268 break;
269 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_S:
270 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getWrapS());
271 break;
272 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_T:
273 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getWrapT());
274 break;
275 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_R:
276 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getWrapR());
277 break;
278 case GL_TEXTURE_IMMUTABLE_FORMAT:
279 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getImmutableFormat());
280 break;
281 case GL_TEXTURE_IMMUTABLE_LEVELS:
282 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getImmutableLevels());
283 break;
284 case GL_TEXTURE_USAGE_ANGLE:
285 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getUsage());
286 break;
287 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_ANISOTROPY_EXT:
288 *params =
289 CastFromSpecialValue<isGLfixed, ParamType>(pname, texture->getMaxAnisotropy());
290 break;
291 case GL_TEXTURE_SWIZZLE_R:
292 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getSwizzleRed());
293 break;
294 case GL_TEXTURE_SWIZZLE_G:
295 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getSwizzleGreen());
296 break;
297 case GL_TEXTURE_SWIZZLE_B:
298 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getSwizzleBlue());
299 break;
300 case GL_TEXTURE_SWIZZLE_A:
301 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getSwizzleAlpha());
302 break;
303 case GL_TEXTURE_BASE_LEVEL:
304 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getBaseLevel());
305 break;
306 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_LEVEL:
307 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getMaxLevel());
308 break;
309 case GL_TEXTURE_MIN_LOD:
310 *params = CastFromSpecialValue<isGLfixed, ParamType>(pname, texture->getMinLod());
311 break;
312 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_LOD:
313 *params = CastFromSpecialValue<isGLfixed, ParamType>(pname, texture->getMaxLod());
314 break;
315 case GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_MODE:
316 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getCompareMode());
317 break;
318 case GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_FUNC:
319 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getCompareFunc());
320 break;
321 case GL_TEXTURE_SRGB_DECODE_EXT:
322 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getSRGBDecode());
323 break;
324 case GL_TEXTURE_FORMAT_SRGB_OVERRIDE_EXT:
325 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getSRGBOverride());
326 break;
327 case GL_DEPTH_STENCIL_TEXTURE_MODE:
328 *params =
329 CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getDepthStencilTextureMode());
330 break;
331 case GL_TEXTURE_CROP_RECT_OES:
332 {
333 const gl::Rectangle &crop = texture->getCrop();
334 params[0] = CastFromSpecialValue<isGLfixed, ParamType>(pname, crop.x);
335 params[1] = CastFromSpecialValue<isGLfixed, ParamType>(pname, crop.y);
336 params[2] = CastFromSpecialValue<isGLfixed, ParamType>(pname, crop.width);
337 params[3] = CastFromSpecialValue<isGLfixed, ParamType>(pname, crop.height);
338 break;
339 }
340 case GL_GENERATE_MIPMAP:
341 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, texture->getGenerateMipmapHint());
342 break;
343 case GL_MEMORY_SIZE_ANGLE:
344 *params = CastFromSpecialValue<isGLfixed, ParamType>(pname, texture->getMemorySize());
345 break;
346 case GL_TEXTURE_BORDER_COLOR:
347 ConvertFromColor<isPureInteger>(texture->getBorderColor(), params);
348 break;
349 case GL_TEXTURE_NATIVE_ID_ANGLE:
350 *params = CastFromSpecialValue<isGLfixed, ParamType>(pname, texture->getNativeID());
351 break;
352 case GL_IMPLEMENTATION_COLOR_READ_FORMAT:
353 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(
354 pname, texture->getImplementationColorReadFormat(context));
355 break;
356 case GL_IMPLEMENTATION_COLOR_READ_TYPE:
357 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(
358 pname, texture->getImplementationColorReadType(context));
359 break;
360 case GL_IMAGE_FORMAT_COMPATIBILITY_TYPE:
361 *params =
362 CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, GL_IMAGE_FORMAT_COMPATIBILITY_BY_SIZE);
363 break;
364 case GL_RESOURCE_INITIALIZED_ANGLE:
365 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(
366 pname, texture->initState() == InitState::Initialized);
367 break;
368 default:
369 UNREACHABLE();
370 break;
371 }
372}

374// this function is needed to handle OES_FIXED_POINT.
375// Some pname values can take in GLfixed values and may need to be converted
376template <bool isGLfixed, typename ReturnType, typename ParamType>
377ReturnType ConvertTexParam(GLenum pname, const ParamType param)
378{
379 if (isGLfixed)
380 {
381 return CastQueryValueTo<ReturnType>(pname,
382 ConvertFixedToFloat(static_cast<GLfixed>(param)));
383 }
384 else
385 {
386 return CastQueryValueTo<ReturnType>(pname, param);
387 }
388}

390template <bool isPureInteger, bool isGLfixed, typename ParamType>
391void SetTexParameterBase(Context *context, Texture *texture, GLenum pname, const ParamType *params)
392{
393 ASSERT(texture != nullptr);
394
395 switch (pname)
396 {
397 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_S:
398 texture->setWrapS(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
399 break;
400 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_T:
401 texture->setWrapT(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
402 break;
403 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_R:
404 texture->setWrapR(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
405 break;
406 case GL_TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER:
407 texture->setMinFilter(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
408 break;
409 case GL_TEXTURE_MAG_FILTER:
410 texture->setMagFilter(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
411 break;
412 case GL_TEXTURE_USAGE_ANGLE:
413 texture->setUsage(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
414 break;
415 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_ANISOTROPY_EXT:
416 texture->setMaxAnisotropy(context,
417 ConvertTexParam<isGLfixed, GLfloat>(pname, params[0]));
418 break;
419 case GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_MODE:
420 texture->setCompareMode(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
421 break;
422 case GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_FUNC:
423 texture->setCompareFunc(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
424 break;
425 case GL_TEXTURE_SWIZZLE_R:
426 texture->setSwizzleRed(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
427 break;
428 case GL_TEXTURE_SWIZZLE_G:
429 texture->setSwizzleGreen(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
430 break;
431 case GL_TEXTURE_SWIZZLE_B:
432 texture->setSwizzleBlue(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
433 break;
434 case GL_TEXTURE_SWIZZLE_A:
435 texture->setSwizzleAlpha(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
436 break;
437 case GL_TEXTURE_BASE_LEVEL:
438 {
439 (void)(texture->setBaseLevel(
440 context, clampCast<GLuint>(CastQueryValueTo<GLint>(pname, params[0]))));
441 break;
442 }
443 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_LEVEL:
444 texture->setMaxLevel(context,
445 clampCast<GLuint>(CastQueryValueTo<GLint>(pname, params[0])));
446 break;
447 case GL_TEXTURE_MIN_LOD:
448 texture->setMinLod(context, CastQueryValueTo<GLfloat>(pname, params[0]));
449 break;
450 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_LOD:
451 texture->setMaxLod(context, CastQueryValueTo<GLfloat>(pname, params[0]));
452 break;
453 case GL_DEPTH_STENCIL_TEXTURE_MODE:
454 texture->setDepthStencilTextureMode(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
455 break;
456 case GL_TEXTURE_SRGB_DECODE_EXT:
457 texture->setSRGBDecode(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
458 break;
459 case GL_TEXTURE_FORMAT_SRGB_OVERRIDE_EXT:
460 texture->setSRGBOverride(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
461 break;
462 case GL_TEXTURE_CROP_RECT_OES:
463 texture->setCrop(gl::Rectangle(ConvertTexParam<isGLfixed, GLint>(pname, params[0]),
464 ConvertTexParam<isGLfixed, GLint>(pname, params[1]),
465 ConvertTexParam<isGLfixed, GLint>(pname, params[2]),
466 ConvertTexParam<isGLfixed, GLint>(pname, params[3])));
467 break;
468 case GL_GENERATE_MIPMAP:
469 texture->setGenerateMipmapHint(ConvertToGLenum(params[0]));
470 break;
471 case GL_TEXTURE_BORDER_COLOR:
472 texture->setBorderColor(context, ConvertToColor<isPureInteger>(params));
473 break;
474 case GL_RESOURCE_INITIALIZED_ANGLE:
475 texture->setInitState(ConvertToBool(params[0]) ? InitState::Initialized
476 : InitState::MayNeedInit);
477 break;
478 default:
479 UNREACHABLE();
480 break;
481 }
482}

484template <bool isPureInteger, typename ParamType>
485void QuerySamplerParameterBase(const Sampler *sampler, GLenum pname, ParamType *params)
486{
487 switch (pname)
488 {
489 case GL_TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER:
490 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, sampler->getMinFilter());
491 break;
492 case GL_TEXTURE_MAG_FILTER:
493 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, sampler->getMagFilter());
494 break;
495 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_S:
496 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, sampler->getWrapS());
497 break;
498 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_T:
499 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, sampler->getWrapT());
500 break;
501 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_R:
502 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, sampler->getWrapR());
503 break;
504 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_ANISOTROPY_EXT:
505 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(pname, sampler->getMaxAnisotropy());
506 break;
507 case GL_TEXTURE_MIN_LOD:
508 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(pname, sampler->getMinLod());
509 break;
510 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_LOD:
511 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(pname, sampler->getMaxLod());
512 break;
513 case GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_MODE:
514 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, sampler->getCompareMode());
515 break;
516 case GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_FUNC:
517 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, sampler->getCompareFunc());
518 break;
519 case GL_TEXTURE_SRGB_DECODE_EXT:
520 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, sampler->getSRGBDecode());
521 break;
522 case GL_TEXTURE_BORDER_COLOR:
523 ConvertFromColor<isPureInteger>(sampler->getBorderColor(), params);
524 break;
525 default:
526 UNREACHABLE();
527 break;
528 }
529}

531template <bool isPureInteger, typename ParamType>
532void SetSamplerParameterBase(Context *context,
533 Sampler *sampler,
534 GLenum pname,
535 const ParamType *params)
536{
537 switch (pname)
538 {
539 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_S:
540 sampler->setWrapS(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
541 break;
542 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_T:
543 sampler->setWrapT(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
544 break;
545 case GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_R:
546 sampler->setWrapR(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
547 break;
548 case GL_TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER:
549 sampler->setMinFilter(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
550 break;
551 case GL_TEXTURE_MAG_FILTER:
552 sampler->setMagFilter(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
553 break;
554 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_ANISOTROPY_EXT:
555 sampler->setMaxAnisotropy(context, CastQueryValueTo<GLfloat>(pname, params[0]));
556 break;
557 case GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_MODE:
558 sampler->setCompareMode(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
559 break;
560 case GL_TEXTURE_COMPARE_FUNC:
561 sampler->setCompareFunc(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
562 break;
563 case GL_TEXTURE_MIN_LOD:
564 sampler->setMinLod(context, CastQueryValueTo<GLfloat>(pname, params[0]));
565 break;
566 case GL_TEXTURE_MAX_LOD:
567 sampler->setMaxLod(context, CastQueryValueTo<GLfloat>(pname, params[0]));
568 break;
569 case GL_TEXTURE_SRGB_DECODE_EXT:
570 sampler->setSRGBDecode(context, ConvertToGLenum(pname, params[0]));
571 break;
572 case GL_TEXTURE_BORDER_COLOR:
573 sampler->setBorderColor(context, ConvertToColor<isPureInteger>(params));
574 break;
575 default:
576 UNREACHABLE();
577 break;
578 }
579
580 sampler->onStateChange(angle::SubjectMessage::ContentsChanged);
581}

583// Warning: you should ensure binding really matches attrib.bindingIndex before using this function.
584template <typename ParamType, typename CurrentDataType, size_t CurrentValueCount>
585void QueryVertexAttribBase(const VertexAttribute &attrib,
586 const VertexBinding &binding,
587 const CurrentDataType (&currentValueData)[CurrentValueCount],
588 GLenum pname,
589 ParamType *params)
590{
591 switch (pname)
592 {
593 case GL_CURRENT_VERTEX_ATTRIB:
594 for (size_t i = 0; i < CurrentValueCount; ++i)
595 {
596 params[i] = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(pname, currentValueData[i]);
597 }
598 break;
599 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_ENABLED:
600 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(pname, static_cast<GLint>(attrib.enabled));
601 break;
602 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_SIZE:
603 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, attrib.format->channelCount);
604 break;
605 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_STRIDE:
606 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, attrib.vertexAttribArrayStride);
607 break;
608 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_TYPE:
609 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(
610 pname, gl::ToGLenum(attrib.format->vertexAttribType));
611 break;
612 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_NORMALIZED:
613 *params =
614 CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(pname, static_cast<GLint>(attrib.format->isNorm()));
615 break;
616 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_BUFFER_BINDING:
617 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, binding.getBuffer().id().value);
618 break;
619 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_DIVISOR:
620 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(pname, binding.getDivisor());
621 break;
622 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_ARRAY_INTEGER:
623 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, attrib.format->isPureInt());
624 break;
625 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_BINDING:
626 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, attrib.bindingIndex);
627 break;
628 case GL_VERTEX_ATTRIB_RELATIVE_OFFSET:
629 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, attrib.relativeOffset);
630 break;
631 default:
632 UNREACHABLE();
633 break;
634 }
635}

637template <typename ParamType>
638void QueryBufferParameterBase(const Buffer *buffer, GLenum pname, ParamType *params)
639{
640 ASSERT(buffer != nullptr);
641
642 switch (pname)
643 {
644 case GL_BUFFER_USAGE:
645 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, ToGLenum(buffer->getUsage()));
646 break;
647 case GL_BUFFER_SIZE:
648 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(pname, buffer->getSize());
649 break;
650 case GL_BUFFER_ACCESS_FLAGS:
651 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, buffer->getAccessFlags());
652 break;
653 case GL_BUFFER_ACCESS_OES:
654 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, buffer->getAccess());
655 break;
656 case GL_BUFFER_MAPPED:
657 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(pname, buffer->isMapped());
658 break;
659 case GL_BUFFER_MAP_OFFSET:
660 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(pname, buffer->getMapOffset());
661 break;
662 case GL_BUFFER_MAP_LENGTH:
663 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(pname, buffer->getMapLength());
664 break;
665 case GL_MEMORY_SIZE_ANGLE:
666 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(pname, buffer->getMemorySize());
667 break;
668 case GL_BUFFER_IMMUTABLE_STORAGE_EXT:
669 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(pname, buffer->isImmutable());
670 break;
671 case GL_BUFFER_STORAGE_FLAGS_EXT:
672 *params = CastFromGLintStateValue<ParamType>(pname, buffer->getStorageExtUsageFlags());
673 break;
674 case GL_RESOURCE_INITIALIZED_ANGLE:
675 *params = CastFromStateValue<ParamType>(
676 pname, ConvertToGLBoolean(buffer->initState() == InitState::Initialized));
677 break;
678 default:
679 UNREACHABLE();
680 break;
681 }
682}
683
684GLint GetCommonVariableProperty(const sh::ShaderVariable &var, GLenum prop)
685{
686 switch (prop)
687 {
688 case GL_TYPE:
689 return clampCast<GLint>(var.type);
690
691 case GL_ARRAY_SIZE:
692 // Queryable variables are guaranteed not to be arrays of arrays or arrays of structs,
693 // see GLES 3.1 spec section 7.3.1.1 page 77.
694 return clampCast<GLint>(var.getBasicTypeElementCount());
695
696 case GL_NAME_LENGTH:
697 // ES31 spec p84: This counts the terminating null char.
698 return clampCast<GLint>(var.name.size() + 1u);
699
700 default:
701 UNREACHABLE();
702 return GL_INVALID_VALUE;
703 }
704}
705
706GLint GetInputResourceProperty(const Program *program, GLuint index, GLenum prop)
707{
708 const sh::ShaderVariable &variable = program->getInputResource(index);
709
710 switch (prop)
711 {
712 case GL_TYPE:
713 case GL_ARRAY_SIZE:
714 return GetCommonVariableProperty(variable, prop);
715
716 case GL_NAME_LENGTH:
717 return clampCast<GLint>(program->getInputResourceName(index).size() + 1u);
718
719 case GL_LOCATION:
720 return variable.isBuiltIn() ? GL_INVALID_INDEX : variable.location;
721
722 // The query is targeted at the set of active input variables used by the first shader stage
723 // of program. If program contains multiple shader stages then input variables from any
724 // stage other than the first will not be enumerated. Since we found the variable to get
725 // this far, we know it exists in the first attached shader stage.
726 case GL_REFERENCED_BY_VERTEX_SHADER:
727 return program->getState().getFirstAttachedShaderStageType() == ShaderType::Vertex;
728 case GL_REFERENCED_BY_FRAGMENT_SHADER:
729 return program->getState().getFirstAttachedShaderStageType() == ShaderType::Fragment;
730 case GL_REFERENCED_BY_COMPUTE_SHADER:
731 return program->getState().getFirstAttachedShaderStageType() == ShaderType::Compute;
732 case GL_REFERENCED_BY_GEOMETRY_SHADER_EXT:
733 return program->getState().getFirstAttachedShaderStageType() == ShaderType::Geometry;
734
735 default:
736 UNREACHABLE();
737 return GL_INVALID_VALUE;
738 }
739}
740
741GLint GetOutputResourceProperty(const Program *program, GLuint index, const GLenum prop)
742{
743 const sh::ShaderVariable &outputVariable = program->getOutputResource(index);
744
745 switch (prop)
746 {
747 case GL_TYPE:
748 case GL_ARRAY_SIZE:
749 return GetCommonVariableProperty(outputVariable, prop);
750
751 case GL_NAME_LENGTH:
752 return clampCast<GLint>(program->getOutputResourceName(index).size() + 1u);
753
754 case GL_LOCATION:
755 return outputVariable.location;
756
757 case GL_LOCATION_INDEX_EXT:
758 // EXT_blend_func_extended
759 if (program->getState().getLastAttachedShaderStageType() == gl::ShaderType::Fragment)
760 {
761 return program->getFragDataIndex(outputVariable.name);
762 }
763 return GL_INVALID_INDEX;
764
765 // The set of active user-defined outputs from the final shader stage in this program. If
766 // the final stage is a Fragment Shader, then this represents the fragment outputs that get
767 // written to individual color buffers. If the program only contains a Compute Shader, then
768 // there are no user-defined outputs.
769 case GL_REFERENCED_BY_VERTEX_SHADER:
770 return program->getState().getLastAttachedShaderStageType() == ShaderType::Vertex;
771 case GL_REFERENCED_BY_FRAGMENT_SHADER:
772 return program->getState().getLastAttachedShaderStageType() == ShaderType::Fragment;
773 case GL_REFERENCED_BY_COMPUTE_SHADER:
774 return program->getState().getLastAttachedShaderStageType() == ShaderType::Compute;
775 case GL_REFERENCED_BY_GEOMETRY_SHADER_EXT:
776 return program->getState().getLastAttachedShaderStageType() == ShaderType::Geometry;
777
778 default:
779 UNREACHABLE();
780 return GL_INVALID_VALUE;
781 }
782}

840template <typename T, typename M>
841GLint FindMaxSize(const std::vector<T> &resources, M member)
842{
843 GLint max = 0;
844 for (const T &resource : resources)
845 {
846 max = std::max(max, clampCast<GLint>((resource.*member).size()));
847 }
848 return max;
849}

851GLint QueryProgramInterfaceMaxNameLength(const Program *program, GLenum programInterface)
852{
853 GLint maxNameLength = 0;
854 switch (programInterface)
855 {
856 case GL_PROGRAM_INPUT:
857 maxNameLength = program->getInputResourceMaxNameSize();
858 break;
859
860 case GL_PROGRAM_OUTPUT:
861 maxNameLength = program->getOutputResourceMaxNameSize();
862 break;
863
864 case GL_UNIFORM:
865 maxNameLength = FindMaxSize(program->getState().getUniforms(), &LinkedUniform::name);
866 break;
867
868 case GL_UNIFORM_BLOCK:
869 return program->getActiveUniformBlockMaxNameLength();
870
871 case GL_BUFFER_VARIABLE:
872 maxNameLength =
873 FindMaxSize(program->getState().getBufferVariables(), &BufferVariable::name);
874 break;
875
876 case GL_SHADER_STORAGE_BLOCK:
877 return program->getActiveShaderStorageBlockMaxNameLength();
878
879 case GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_VARYING:
880 return clampCast<GLint>(program->getTransformFeedbackVaryingMaxLength());
881
882 default:
883 UNREACHABLE();
884 return 0;
885 }
886 // This length includes an extra character for the null terminator.
887 return (maxNameLength == 0 ? 0 : maxNameLength + 1);
888}

967void GetShaderVariableBufferResourceProperty(const ShaderVariableBuffer &buffer,
968 GLenum pname,
969 GLint *params,
970 GLsizei bufSize,
971 GLsizei *outputPosition)
972
973{
974 switch (pname)
975 {
976 case GL_BUFFER_BINDING:
977 params[(*outputPosition)++] = buffer.binding;
978 break;
979 case GL_BUFFER_DATA_SIZE:
980 params[(*outputPosition)++] = clampCast<GLint>(buffer.dataSize);
981 break;
982 case GL_NUM_ACTIVE_VARIABLES:
983 params[(*outputPosition)++] = buffer.numActiveVariables();
984 break;
985 case GL_ACTIVE_VARIABLES:
986 for (size_t memberIndex = 0;
987 memberIndex < buffer.memberIndexes.size() && *outputPosition < bufSize;
988 ++memberIndex)
989 {
990 params[(*outputPosition)++] = clampCast<GLint>(buffer.memberIndexes[memberIndex]);
991 }
992 break;
993 case GL_REFERENCED_BY_VERTEX_SHADER:
994 params[(*outputPosition)++] = static_cast<GLint>(buffer.isActive(ShaderType::Vertex));
995 break;
996 case GL_REFERENCED_BY_FRAGMENT_SHADER:
997 params[(*outputPosition)++] = static_cast<GLint>(buffer.isActive(ShaderType::Fragment));
998 break;
999 case GL_REFERENCED_BY_COMPUTE_SHADER:
1000 params[(*outputPosition)++] = static_cast<GLint>(buffer.isActive(ShaderType::Compute));
1001 break;
1002 case GL_REFERENCED_BY_GEOMETRY_SHADER_EXT:
1003 params[(*outputPosition)++] = static_cast<GLint>(buffer.isActive(ShaderType::Geometry));
1004 break;
1005 default:
1006 UNREACHABLE();
1007 break;
1008 }
1009}

1092void QueryFramebufferAttachmentParameteriv(const Context *context,
1093 const Framebuffer *framebuffer,
1094 GLenum attachment,
1095 GLenum pname,
1096 GLint *params)
1097{
1098 ASSERT(framebuffer);
1099
1100 const FramebufferAttachment *attachmentObject = framebuffer->getAttachment(context, attachment);
1101
1102 if (attachmentObject == nullptr)
1103 {
1104 // ES 2.0.25 spec pg 127 states that if the value of FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_TYPE
1105 // is NONE, then querying any other pname will generate INVALID_ENUM.
1106
1107 // ES 3.0.2 spec pg 235 states that if the attachment type is none,
1108 // GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_NAME will return zero and be an
1109 // INVALID_OPERATION for all other pnames
1110
1111 switch (pname)
1112 {
1113 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_TYPE:
1114 *params = GL_NONE;
1115 break;
1116
1117 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_NAME:
1118 *params = 0;
1119 break;
1120
1121 default:
1122 UNREACHABLE();
1123 break;
1124 }
1125
1126 return;
1127 }
1128
1129 switch (pname)
1130 {
1131 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_TYPE:
1132 *params = attachmentObject->type();
1133 break;
1134
1135 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_OBJECT_NAME:
1136 *params = attachmentObject->id();
1137 break;
1138
1139 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_LEVEL:
1140 *params = attachmentObject->mipLevel();
1141 break;
1142
1143 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_CUBE_MAP_FACE:
1144 {
1145 TextureTarget face = attachmentObject->cubeMapFace();
1146 if (face != TextureTarget::InvalidEnum)
1147 {
1148 *params = ToGLenum(attachmentObject->cubeMapFace());
1149 }
1150 else
1151 {
1152 // This happens when the attachment isn't a texture cube map face
1153 *params = GL_NONE;
1154 }
1155 }
1156 break;
1157
1158 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_RED_SIZE:
1159 *params = attachmentObject->getRedSize();
1160 break;
1161
1162 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_GREEN_SIZE:
1163 *params = attachmentObject->getGreenSize();
1164 break;
1165
1166 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_BLUE_SIZE:
1167 *params = attachmentObject->getBlueSize();
1168 break;
1169
1170 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_ALPHA_SIZE:
1171 *params = attachmentObject->getAlphaSize();
1172 break;
1173
1174 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_DEPTH_SIZE:
1175 *params = attachmentObject->getDepthSize();
1176 break;
1177
1178 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_STENCIL_SIZE:
1179 *params = attachmentObject->getStencilSize();
1180 break;
1181
1182 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_COMPONENT_TYPE:
1183 *params = attachmentObject->getComponentType();
1184 break;
1185
1186 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_COLOR_ENCODING:
1187 *params = attachmentObject->getColorEncoding();
1188 break;
1189
1190 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_LAYER:
1191 *params = attachmentObject->layer();
1192 break;
1193
1194 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_NUM_VIEWS_OVR:
1195 *params = attachmentObject->getNumViews();
1196 break;
1197
1198 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_BASE_VIEW_INDEX_OVR:
1199 *params = attachmentObject->getBaseViewIndex();
1200 break;
1201
1202 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_LAYERED_EXT:
1203 *params = attachmentObject->isLayered();
1204 break;
1205
1206 case GL_FRAMEBUFFER_ATTACHMENT_TEXTURE_SAMPLES_EXT:
1207 if (attachmentObject->type() == GL_TEXTURE)
1208 {
1209 *params = attachmentObject->getSamples();
1210 }
1211 else
1212 {
1213 *params = 0;
1214 }
1215 break;
1216
1217 default:
1218 UNREACHABLE();
1219 break;
1220 }
1221}

1247void QueryProgramiv(Context *context, const Program *program, GLenum pname, GLint *params)
1248{
1249 ASSERT(program != nullptr || pname == GL_COMPLETION_STATUS_KHR);
1250
1251 switch (pname)
1252 {
1253 case GL_DELETE_STATUS:
1254 *params = program->isFlaggedForDeletion();
1255 return;
1256 case GL_LINK_STATUS:
1257 *params = program->isLinked();
1258 return;
1259 case GL_COMPLETION_STATUS_KHR:
1260 if (context->isContextLost())
1261 {
1262 *params = GL_TRUE;
1263 }
1264 else
1265 {
1266 *params = program->isLinking() ? GL_FALSE : GL_TRUE;
1267 }
1268 return;
1269 case GL_VALIDATE_STATUS:
1270 *params = program->isValidated();
1271 return;
1272 case GL_INFO_LOG_LENGTH:
1273 *params = program->getExecutable().getInfoLogLength();
1274 return;
1275 case GL_ATTACHED_SHADERS:
1276 *params = program->getAttachedShadersCount();
1277 return;
1278 case GL_ACTIVE_ATTRIBUTES:
1279 *params = program->getActiveAttributeCount();
1280 return;
1281 case GL_ACTIVE_ATTRIBUTE_MAX_LENGTH:
1282 *params = program->getActiveAttributeMaxLength();
1283 return;
1284 case GL_ACTIVE_UNIFORMS:
1285 *params = program->getActiveUniformCount();
1286 return;
1287 case GL_ACTIVE_UNIFORM_MAX_LENGTH:
1288 *params = program->getActiveUniformMaxLength();
1289 return;
1290 case GL_PROGRAM_BINARY_LENGTH_OES:
1291 *params = context->getCaps().programBinaryFormats.empty()
1292 ? 0
1293 : program->getBinaryLength(context);
1294 return;
1295 case GL_ACTIVE_UNIFORM_BLOCKS:
1296 *params = program->getActiveUniformBlockCount();
1297 return;
1298 case GL_ACTIVE_UNIFORM_BLOCK_MAX_NAME_LENGTH:
1299 *params = program->getActiveUniformBlockMaxNameLength();
1300 break;
1301 case GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_BUFFER_MODE:
1302 *params = program->getTransformFeedbackBufferMode();
1303 break;
1304 case GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_VARYINGS:
1305 *params = clampCast<GLint>(program->getTransformFeedbackVaryingCount());
1306 break;
1307 case GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_VARYING_MAX_LENGTH:
1308 *params = program->getTransformFeedbackVaryingMaxLength();
1309 break;
1310 case GL_PROGRAM_BINARY_RETRIEVABLE_HINT:
1311 *params = program->getBinaryRetrievableHint();
1312 break;
1313 case GL_PROGRAM_SEPARABLE:
1314 // From es31cSeparateShaderObjsTests.cpp:
1315 // ProgramParameteri PROGRAM_SEPARABLE
1316 // NOTE: The query for PROGRAM_SEPARABLE must query latched
1317 // state. In other words, the state of the binary after
1318 // it was linked. So in the tests below, the queries
1319 // should return the default state GL_FALSE since the
1320 // program has no linked binary.
1321 *params = program->isSeparable() && program->isLinked();
1322 break;
1323 case GL_COMPUTE_WORK_GROUP_SIZE:
1324 {
1325 const sh::WorkGroupSize &localSize = program->getComputeShaderLocalSize();
1326 params[0] = localSize[0];
1327 params[1] = localSize[1];
1328 params[2] = localSize[2];
1329 }
1330 break;
1331 case GL_ACTIVE_ATOMIC_COUNTER_BUFFERS:
1332 *params = program->getActiveAtomicCounterBufferCount();
1333 break;
1334 case GL_GEOMETRY_LINKED_INPUT_TYPE_EXT:
1335 *params = ToGLenum(program->getGeometryShaderInputPrimitiveType());
1336 break;
1337 case GL_GEOMETRY_LINKED_OUTPUT_TYPE_EXT:
1338 *params = ToGLenum(program->getGeometryShaderOutputPrimitiveType());
1339 break;
1340 case GL_GEOMETRY_LINKED_VERTICES_OUT_EXT:
1341 *params = program->getGeometryShaderMaxVertices();
1342 break;
1343 case GL_GEOMETRY_SHADER_INVOCATIONS_EXT:
1344 *params = program->getGeometryShaderInvocations();
1345 break;
1346 default:
1347 UNREACHABLE();
1348 break;
1349 }
1350}

1352void QueryRenderbufferiv(const Context *context,
1353 const Renderbuffer *renderbuffer,
1354 GLenum pname,
1355 GLint *params)
1356{
1357 ASSERT(renderbuffer != nullptr);
1358
1359 switch (pname)
1360 {
1361 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_WIDTH:
1362 *params = renderbuffer->getWidth();
1363 break;
1364 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_HEIGHT:
1365 *params = renderbuffer->getHeight();
1366 break;
1367 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_INTERNAL_FORMAT:
1368 // Special case the WebGL 1 DEPTH_STENCIL format.
1369 if (context->isWebGL1() &&
1370 renderbuffer->getFormat().info->internalFormat == GL_DEPTH24_STENCIL8)
1371 {
1372 *params = GL_DEPTH_STENCIL;
1373 }
1374 else
1375 {
1376 *params = renderbuffer->getFormat().info->internalFormat;
1377 }
1378 break;
1379 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_RED_SIZE:
1380 *params = renderbuffer->getRedSize();
1381 break;
1382 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_GREEN_SIZE:
1383 *params = renderbuffer->getGreenSize();
1384 break;
1385 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_BLUE_SIZE:
1386 *params = renderbuffer->getBlueSize();
1387 break;
1388 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_ALPHA_SIZE:
1389 *params = renderbuffer->getAlphaSize();
1390 break;
1391 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_DEPTH_SIZE:
1392 *params = renderbuffer->getDepthSize();
1393 break;
1394 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_STENCIL_SIZE:
1395 *params = renderbuffer->getStencilSize();
1396 break;
1397 case GL_RENDERBUFFER_SAMPLES_ANGLE:
1398 *params = renderbuffer->getState().getSamples();
1399 break;
1400 case GL_MEMORY_SIZE_ANGLE:
1401 *params = renderbuffer->getMemorySize();
1402 break;
1403 case GL_IMPLEMENTATION_COLOR_READ_FORMAT:
1404 *params = static_cast<GLint>(renderbuffer->getImplementationColorReadFormat(context));
1405 break;
1406 case GL_IMPLEMENTATION_COLOR_READ_TYPE:
1407 *params = static_cast<GLint>(renderbuffer->getImplementationColorReadType(context));
1408 break;
1409 case GL_RESOURCE_INITIALIZED_ANGLE:
1410 *params = (renderbuffer->initState(ImageIndex()) == InitState::Initialized);
1411 break;
1412 default:
1413 UNREACHABLE();
1414 break;
1415 }
1416}

1418void QueryShaderiv(const Context *context, Shader *shader, GLenum pname, GLint *params)
1419{
1420 ASSERT(shader != nullptr || pname == GL_COMPLETION_STATUS_KHR);
1421
1422 switch (pname)
1423 {
1424 case GL_SHADER_TYPE:
1425 *params = static_cast<GLint>(ToGLenum(shader->getType()));
1426 return;
1427 case GL_DELETE_STATUS:
1428 *params = shader->isFlaggedForDeletion();
1429 return;
1430 case GL_COMPILE_STATUS:
1431 *params = shader->isCompiled() ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
1432 return;
1433 case GL_COMPLETION_STATUS_KHR:
1434 if (context->isContextLost())
1435 {
1436 *params = GL_TRUE;
1437 }
1438 else
1439 {
1440 *params = shader->isCompleted() ? GL_TRUE : GL_FALSE;
1441 }
1442 return;
1443 case GL_INFO_LOG_LENGTH:
1444 *params = shader->getInfoLogLength();
1445 return;
1446 case GL_SHADER_SOURCE_LENGTH:
1447 *params = shader->getSourceLength();
1448 return;
1449 case GL_TRANSLATED_SHADER_SOURCE_LENGTH_ANGLE:
1450 *params = shader->getTranslatedSourceWithDebugInfoLength();
1451 return;
1452 default:
1453 UNREACHABLE();
1454 break;
1455 }
1456}

1597void QueryInternalFormativ(const TextureCaps &format, GLenum pname, GLsizei bufSize, GLint *params)
1598{
1599 switch (pname)
1600 {
1601 case GL_NUM_SAMPLE_COUNTS:
1602 if (bufSize != 0)
1603 {
1604 *params = clampCast<GLint>(format.sampleCounts.size());
1605 }
1606 break;
1607
1608 case GL_SAMPLES:
1609 {
1610 size_t returnCount = std::min<size_t>(bufSize, format.sampleCounts.size());
1611 auto sampleReverseIt = format.sampleCounts.rbegin();
1612 for (size_t sampleIndex = 0; sampleIndex < returnCount; ++sampleIndex)
1613 {
1614 params[sampleIndex] = *sampleReverseIt++;
1615 }
1616 }
1617 break;
1618
1619 default:
1620 UNREACHABLE();
1621 break;
1622 }
1623}

1652angle::Result QuerySynciv(const Context *context,
1653 const Sync *sync,
1654 GLenum pname,
1655 GLsizei bufSize,
1656 GLsizei *length,
1657 GLint *values)
1658{
1659 ASSERT(sync != nullptr || pname == GL_SYNC_STATUS);
1660
1661 // All queries return one value, exit early if the buffer can't fit anything.
1662 if (bufSize < 1)
1663 {
1664 if (length != nullptr)
1665 {
1666 *length = 0;
1667 }
1668 return angle::Result::Continue;
1669 }
1670
1671 switch (pname)
1672 {
1673 case GL_OBJECT_TYPE:
1674 *values = clampCast<GLint>(GL_SYNC_FENCE);
1675 break;
1676 case GL_SYNC_CONDITION:
1677 *values = clampCast<GLint>(sync->getCondition());
1678 break;
1679 case GL_SYNC_FLAGS:
1680 *values = clampCast<GLint>(sync->getFlags());
1681 break;
1682 case GL_SYNC_STATUS:
1683 if (context->isContextLost())
1684 {
1685 *values = GL_SIGNALED;
1686 }
1687 else
1688 {
1689 ANGLE_TRY(sync->getStatus(context, values));
1690 }
1691 break;
1692
1693 default:
1694 UNREACHABLE();
1695 break;
1696 }
1697
1698 if (length != nullptr)
1699 {
1700 *length = 1;
1701 }
1702
1703 return angle::Result::Continue;
1704}

1824GLint GetUniformResourceProperty(const Program *program, GLuint index, const GLenum prop)
1825{
1826 const auto &uniform = program->getUniformByIndex(index);
1827 GLenum resourceProp = GetUniformPropertyEnum(prop);
1828 switch (resourceProp)
1829 {
1830 case GL_TYPE:
1831 case GL_ARRAY_SIZE:
1832 case GL_NAME_LENGTH:
1833 return GetCommonVariableProperty(uniform, resourceProp);
1834
1835 case GL_LOCATION:
1836 return program->getUniformLocation(uniform.name).value;
1837
1838 case GL_BLOCK_INDEX:
1839 return (uniform.isAtomicCounter() ? -1 : uniform.bufferIndex);
1840
1841 case GL_OFFSET:
1842 return uniform.blockInfo.offset;
1843
1844 case GL_ARRAY_STRIDE:
1845 return uniform.blockInfo.arrayStride;
1846
1847 case GL_MATRIX_STRIDE:
1848 return uniform.blockInfo.matrixStride;
1849
1850 case GL_IS_ROW_MAJOR:
1851 return static_cast<GLint>(uniform.blockInfo.isRowMajorMatrix);
1852
1853 case GL_REFERENCED_BY_VERTEX_SHADER:
1854 return uniform.isActive(ShaderType::Vertex);
1855
1856 case GL_REFERENCED_BY_FRAGMENT_SHADER:
1857 return uniform.isActive(ShaderType::Fragment);
1858
1859 case GL_REFERENCED_BY_COMPUTE_SHADER:
1860 return uniform.isActive(ShaderType::Compute);
1861
1862 case GL_REFERENCED_BY_GEOMETRY_SHADER_EXT:
1863 return uniform.isActive(ShaderType::Geometry);
1864
1865 case GL_ATOMIC_COUNTER_BUFFER_INDEX:
1866 return (uniform.isAtomicCounter() ? uniform.bufferIndex : -1);
1867
1868 default:
1869 UNREACHABLE();
1870 return 0;
1871 }
1872}

2018
2019void QueryProgramResourceiv(const Program *program,
2020 GLenum programInterface,
2021 GLuint index,
2022 GLsizei propCount,
2023 const GLenum *props,
2024 GLsizei bufSize,
2025 GLsizei *length,
2026 GLint *params)
2027{
2028 if (!program->isLinked())
2029 {
2030 return;
2031 }
2032
2033 if (length != nullptr)
2034 {
2035 *length = 0;
2036 }
2037
2038 if (bufSize == 0)
2039 {
2040 // No room to write the results
2041 return;
2042 }
2043
2044 GLsizei pos = 0;
2045 for (GLsizei i = 0; i < propCount; i++)
2046 {
2047 switch (programInterface)
2048 {
2049 case GL_PROGRAM_INPUT:
2050 params[i] = GetInputResourceProperty(program, index, props[i]);
2051 ++pos;
2052 break;
2053
2054 case GL_PROGRAM_OUTPUT:
2055 params[i] = GetOutputResourceProperty(program, index, props[i]);
2056 ++pos;
2057 break;
2058
2059 case GL_UNIFORM:
2060 params[i] = GetUniformResourceProperty(program, index, props[i]);
2061 ++pos;
2062 break;
2063
2064 case GL_BUFFER_VARIABLE:
2065 params[i] = GetBufferVariableResourceProperty(program, index, props[i]);
2066 ++pos;
2067 break;
2068
2069 case GL_UNIFORM_BLOCK:
2070 GetUniformBlockResourceProperty(program, index, props[i], params, bufSize, &pos);
2071 break;
2072
2073 case GL_SHADER_STORAGE_BLOCK:
2074 GetShaderStorageBlockResourceProperty(program, index, props[i], params, bufSize,
2075 &pos);
2076 break;
2077
2078 case GL_ATOMIC_COUNTER_BUFFER:
2079 GetAtomicCounterBufferResourceProperty(program, index, props[i], params, bufSize,
2080 &pos);
2081 break;
2082
2083 case GL_TRANSFORM_FEEDBACK_VARYING:
2084 params[i] = GetTransformFeedbackVaryingResourceProperty(program, index, props[i]);
2085 ++pos;
2086 break;
2087
2088 default:
2089 UNREACHABLE();
2090 params[i] = GL_INVALID_VALUE;
2091 }
2092 if (pos == bufSize)
2093 {
2094 // Most properties return one value, but GL_ACTIVE_VARIABLES returns an array of values.
2095 // This checks not to break buffer bounds for such case.
2096 break;
2097 }
2098 }
2099
2100 if (length != nullptr)
2101 {
2102 *length = pos;
2103 }
2104}

2161ClientVertexArrayType ParamToVertexArrayType(GLenum param)
2162{

2243void SetLightParameters(GLES1State *state,
2244 GLenum light,
2245 LightParameter pname,
2246 const GLfloat *params)
2247{
2248 uint32_t lightIndex = light - GL_LIGHT0;
2249
2250 LightParameters &lightParams = state->lightParameters(lightIndex);
2251
2252 switch (pname)
2253 {
2254 case LightParameter::Ambient:
2255 lightParams.ambient = ColorF::fromData(params);
2256 break;
2257 case LightParameter::Diffuse:
2258 lightParams.diffuse = ColorF::fromData(params);
2259 break;
2260 case LightParameter::Specular:
2261 lightParams.specular = ColorF::fromData(params);
2262 break;
2263 case LightParameter::Position:
2264 {
2265 angle::Mat4 mv = state->getModelviewMatrix();
2266 angle::Vector4 transformedPos =
2267 mv.product(angle::Vector4(params[0], params[1], params[2], params[3]));
2268 lightParams.position[0] = transformedPos[0];
2269 lightParams.position[1] = transformedPos[1];
2270 lightParams.position[2] = transformedPos[2];
2271 lightParams.position[3] = transformedPos[3];
2272 }
2273 break;
2274 case LightParameter::SpotDirection:
2275 {
2276 angle::Mat4 mv = state->getModelviewMatrix();
2277 angle::Vector4 transformedPos =
2278 mv.product(angle::Vector4(params[0], params[1], params[2], 0.0f));
2279 lightParams.direction[0] = transformedPos[0];
2280 lightParams.direction[1] = transformedPos[1];
2281 lightParams.direction[2] = transformedPos[2];
2282 }
2283 break;
2284 case LightParameter::SpotExponent:
2285 lightParams.spotlightExponent = *params;
2286 break;
2287 case LightParameter::SpotCutoff:
2288 lightParams.spotlightCutoffAngle = *params;
2289 break;
2290 case LightParameter::ConstantAttenuation:
2291 lightParams.attenuationConst = *params;
2292 break;
2293 case LightParameter::LinearAttenuation:
2294 lightParams.attenuationLinear = *params;
2295 break;
2296 case LightParameter::QuadraticAttenuation:
2297 lightParams.attenuationQuadratic = *params;
2298 break;
2299 default:
2300 return;

3772
3773void QueryProgramPipelineiv(const Context *context,
3774 ProgramPipeline *programPipeline,
3775 GLenum pname,
3776 GLint *params)
3777{
3778 if (!params)
3779 {
3780 // Can't write the result anywhere, so just return immediately.
3781 return;
3782 }
3783
3784 switch (pname)
3785 {
3786 case GL_ACTIVE_PROGRAM:
3787 {
3788 // the name of the active program object of the program pipeline object is returned in
3789 // params
3790 *params = 0;
3791 if (programPipeline)
3792 {
3793 const Program *program = programPipeline->getActiveShaderProgram();
3794 if (program)
3795 {
3796 *params = program->id().value;
3797 }
3798 }
3799 break;
3800 }
3801
3802 case GL_VERTEX_SHADER:
3803 {
3804 // the name of the current program object for the vertex shader type of the program
3805 // pipeline object is returned in params
3806 *params = 0;
3807 if (programPipeline)
3808 {
3809 const Program *program = programPipeline->getShaderProgram(ShaderType::Vertex);
3810 if (program)
3811 {
3812 *params = program->id().value;
3813 }
3814 }
3815 break;
3816 }
3817
3818 case GL_FRAGMENT_SHADER:
3819 {
3820 // the name of the current program object for the fragment shader type of the program
3821 // pipeline object is returned in params
3822 *params = 0;
3823 if (programPipeline)
3824 {
3825 const Program *program = programPipeline->getShaderProgram(ShaderType::Fragment);
3826 if (program)
3827 {
3828 *params = program->id().value;
3829 }
3830 }
3831 break;
3832 }
3833
3834 case GL_COMPUTE_SHADER:
3835 {
3836 // the name of the current program object for the compute shader type of the program
3837 // pipeline object is returned in params
3838 *params = 0;
3839 if (programPipeline)
3840 {
3841 const Program *program = programPipeline->getShaderProgram(ShaderType::Compute);
3842 if (program)
3843 {
3844 *params = program->id().value;
3845 }
3846 }
3847 break;
3848 }
3849
3850 case GL_INFO_LOG_LENGTH:
3851 {
3852 // the length of the info log, including the null terminator, is returned in params. If
3853 // there is no info log, zero is returned.
3854 *params = 0;
3855 if (programPipeline)
3856 {
3857 *params = programPipeline->getExecutable().getInfoLogLength();
3858 }
3859 break;
3860 }
3861
3862 case GL_VALIDATE_STATUS:
3863 {
3864 // the validation status of pipeline, as determined by glValidateProgramPipeline, is
3865 // returned in params
3866 *params = 0;
3867 if (programPipeline)
3868 {
3869 *params = programPipeline->isValid();
3870 }
3871 break;
3872 }
3873
3874 default:
3875 break;
3876 }
3877}

4010void QueryContextAttrib(const gl::Context *context, EGLint attribute, EGLint *value)
4011{
4012 switch (attribute)
4013 {
4014 case EGL_CONFIG_ID:
4015 if (context->getConfig() != EGL_NO_CONFIG_KHR)
4016 {

4018 }
4019 else
4020 {
4021 *value = 0;
4022 }
4023 break;
4024 case EGL_CONTEXT_CLIENT_TYPE:
4025 *value = context->getClientType();
4026 break;
4027 case EGL_CONTEXT_CLIENT_VERSION:
4028 *value = context->getClientMajorVersion();
4029 break;
4030 case EGL_RENDER_BUFFER:

4032 break;

4035 break;
4036 case EGL_CONTEXT_PRIORITY_LEVEL_IMG:

4045egl::Error QuerySurfaceAttrib(const Display *display,
4046 const Surface *surface,
4047 EGLint attribute,
4048 EGLint *value)
4049{
4050 switch (attribute)
4051 {
4052 case EGL_GL_COLORSPACE:
4053 *value = surface->getGLColorspace();
4054 break;
4055 case EGL_VG_ALPHA_FORMAT:
4056 *value = surface->getVGAlphaFormat();
4057 break;
4058 case EGL_VG_COLORSPACE:
4059 *value = surface->getVGColorspace();
4060 break;
4061 case EGL_CONFIG_ID:
4062 *value = surface->getConfig()->configID;
4063 break;
4064 case EGL_HEIGHT:
4065 ANGLE_TRY(surface->getUserHeight(display, value));
4066 break;
4067 case EGL_HORIZONTAL_RESOLUTION:
4068 *value = surface->getHorizontalResolution();
4069 break;
4070 case EGL_LARGEST_PBUFFER:
4071 // The EGL spec states that value is not written if the surface is not a pbuffer
4072 if (surface->getType() == EGL_PBUFFER_BIT)
4073 {
4074 *value = surface->getLargestPbuffer();
4075 }
4076 break;
4077 case EGL_MIPMAP_TEXTURE:
4078 // The EGL spec states that value is not written if the surface is not a pbuffer
4079 if (surface->getType() == EGL_PBUFFER_BIT)
4080 {
4081 *value = surface->getMipmapTexture();
4082 }
4083 break;
4084 case EGL_MIPMAP_LEVEL:
4085 // The EGL spec states that value is not written if the surface is not a pbuffer
4086 if (surface->getType() == EGL_PBUFFER_BIT)
4087 {
4088 *value = surface->getMipmapLevel();
4089 }
4090 break;
4091 case EGL_MULTISAMPLE_RESOLVE:
4092 *value = surface->getMultisampleResolve();
4093 break;
4094 case EGL_PIXEL_ASPECT_RATIO:
4095 *value = surface->getPixelAspectRatio();
4096 break;
4097 case EGL_RENDER_BUFFER:
4098 *value = surface->getRenderBuffer();
4099 break;
4100 case EGL_SWAP_BEHAVIOR:
4101 *value = surface->getSwapBehavior();
4102 break;
4103 case EGL_TEXTURE_FORMAT:
4104 // The EGL spec states that value is not written if the surface is not a pbuffer
4105 if (surface->getType() == EGL_PBUFFER_BIT)
4106 {
4107 *value = ToEGLenum(surface->getTextureFormat());
4108 }
4109 break;
4110 case EGL_TEXTURE_TARGET:
4111 // The EGL spec states that value is not written if the surface is not a pbuffer
4112 if (surface->getType() == EGL_PBUFFER_BIT)
4113 {
4114 *value = surface->getTextureTarget();
4115 }
4116 break;
4117 case EGL_VERTICAL_RESOLUTION:
4118 *value = surface->getVerticalResolution();
4119 break;
4120 case EGL_WIDTH:
4121 ANGLE_TRY(surface->getUserWidth(display, value));
4122 break;
4123 case EGL_POST_SUB_BUFFER_SUPPORTED_NV:
4124 *value = surface->isPostSubBufferSupported();
4125 break;
4126 case EGL_FIXED_SIZE_ANGLE:
4127 *value = surface->isFixedSize();
4128 break;
4129 case EGL_FLEXIBLE_SURFACE_COMPATIBILITY_SUPPORTED_ANGLE:
4130 *value = surface->flexibleSurfaceCompatibilityRequested();
4131 break;
4132 case EGL_SURFACE_ORIENTATION_ANGLE:
4133 *value = surface->getOrientation();
4134 break;
4135 case EGL_DIRECT_COMPOSITION_ANGLE:
4136 *value = surface->directComposition();
4137 break;
4138 case EGL_ROBUST_RESOURCE_INITIALIZATION_ANGLE:
4139 *value = surface->isRobustResourceInitEnabled();
4140 break;
4141 case EGL_TIMESTAMPS_ANDROID:
4142 *value = surface->isTimestampsEnabled();
4143 break;
4144 default:
4145 UNREACHABLE();
4146 break;
4147 }
